1. Packer is a tool to build AMIs

2. Previously to install softwares, we used terraform with shell commands. The alternative is packer.

3. Packer is a commandline tool that can build AWS AMIs based on template.

4. Instead of installing software after booting up the instance, you can create an AMI with all the necessary softwares on. This can spped up the boot time of instances.

5. One alternative is docker. We can also build AMIs with docker.
